px;line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">During his Spaces chat, Bill announced tha=
t he and his Pershing
Square affiliates were sweetening the pot, offering to buy $900 million in =
Howard Hughes stock, directly from the company, at $90 per share=E2=80=94a =
<em>46 percent</em> premium to the unaffected share price. (The stock is no=
w trading around $74 per share.) =E2=80=9CNormally, you would see premiums =
like this in change-of-control, going-private transactions,=E2=80=9D Bill s=
aid. =E2=80=9CHere, we are simply buying stock in the company.=E2=80=9D The=
 enhanced bid represented a modest ~6 percent increase from the $85 per sha=
re they had
previously offered, but it=E2=80=99s a far simpler transaction.=C2=A0</p><p=
 style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">Bill already has the cash ready to go=E2=80=94no outside fin=
ancing required. If the proposal is accepted by the special committee, Bill=
 and his affiliates would increase their ownership stake in Howard Hughes t=
o 48 percent. Other aspects of the initial proposal stay the same: Bill and=
 his crew would take over the responsibility of using the company=E2=80=99s
cash flow, plus his new $900 million, to try to make all sorts of clever ac=
quisitions, like Buffett, while leaving the company=E2=80=99s existing mana=
gement in place at the real estate level. (Buffett, of course, has a cash h=
oard of $334 billion, <em>far</em> more than what Bill would have at his di=
sposal.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;">In exchange for his =E2=80=9Cservices,=E2=80=9D Bill is as=
king for a 1.5 percent annual management fee based on the market value of t=
he
company, which is now about $3.7 billion=E2=80=94so an annual fee of about =
$55 million=E2=80=94which would increase if the market value increases. He=
=E2=80=99s also committing to hold on to the stock =E2=80=9Cforever,=E2=80=
=9D as he said on X, and to not squeeze out the other public shareholders. =
He additionally said the company would not buy back its stock without the a=
pproval of the board of directors, a pledge of sorts that Bill &amp; Co. wo=
n=E2=80=99t increase their stake above 50 percent.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
